text.tspan: The Nine Fingers has a weak reputation
towards outsiders due to their notorious
hand-to-hand combat ability, but on the
battlefield they are considered powerful.
During combat they always stick with each
other till the last moment.
The Nine Fingers are unfamiliar with using
firearms because these gladiators only used
swords, shields, and whips to protect
themselves while trapped in Fidelia’s
arena. As a result, they fight primarily in
surprise hand-to-hand combat to draw the
opponent into the hand-to-hand combat
battlefield.
The Nine Fingers work as
mercenaries, stealing weapons and
receiving money, robbing survivors of
other groups by traveling back and
forth along rivers, catching fish for
food, and so on. They are not afraid
of risking their lives to secure
essential supplies such as food, water,
weapons, etc. They are willing to go
to any length to survive.
Leopart the 3rd was the champion among the
gladiators for the longest time. Despite solidifying his
position as the strongest, he was convinced that the
empire would eventually force a generational change.
He fled the empire for freedom and joined forces with
other slave fighters in the same arena. Destroyed the
space and looted the empire’s weapons.
The Fidelian Empire ran several arenas for
its noble class' entertainment, and 'fighter
slaves' were often called gladiators who
fought in these arenas. The gladiators had
the characteristics of both slaves and
entertainers. They were treated like used
merchandise that was consumed and
vanished quickly.
The Nine Fingers indicates Leopart
the 3rd and 8 comrades who led
the process of fleeting the empire.
Nine Fingers is primarily consisted
of gladiators from Fidelian’s arena,
slave workers, and a few random
civilians who joined along the way.
New beginnings
Biff was always concerned about betrayal, and
the empire didn't care who became the
Hunters' leader, so he didn't try to train overly
strong subordinates. Given the nature of the
request that the commanding group accepts in
the first place, he is well aware that each
member's excessively high combat ability is
somewhat poisonous for himself.
The average soldiers in the Hunters can
barely handle old-generation firearms.
However, they still need more support from
the empire. The truth is a few members
have more fighting power than others,
including Biff, and they take advantage of
corruption by being the gang's leader.
Biff is the Hunters leader, and about ten
‘loyal corrupted convicts closely follow
him. Hunters is an empire-monitored
organization, so it cannot be called an
outlaw group. They have no intention of
following rules, and their level of
discipline is shallow.
The Fidelian Empire selects
some of its slaves and sends
them to the Hunters as a
revival ceremony to replace
their troops regularly. This is
due to the empire’s view of
the Hunters as
indispensable.
For operations that are likely
to be dangerous, material
support is provided most for
old-generation weapons and
exclusively not for Titans.
They receive almost all requests from the
empire, and because they rarely interact
with other groups, their operating funds
depend entirely on the empire.
The former slave camp’s
mercenary commander, ‘Biff,’ is
greedy and cunning. The empire
previously enslaved him, but the
empire recognized him for his
strength and proper manners. He
was freed and given the task of
leading the Hunters.
The missions assigned to the
Hunters are usually dirty and
brutal that the empire cannot
openly perform, primarily hunting
runaway enslaved people and
suppressing survivors’ settlements
that do not obey the empire with
little force.
The Fidelian Empire is
experiencing a chronic shortage
of troops as it works to
strengthen the organization.
The empire, which does not
have enough resources to
maintain and operate a regular
army, is accustomed to hiring
and using insufficient soldiers.
The Hunters are an exclusive
military group dedicated to
relatively less complicated
chores.
Their weapons are mainly guns from the
pre-war era. Although gunpowder and
bullets are obtained by looting, they are
often procured by themselves, specifically
by moving to and from the desert. They are
armed with such weapons and have
combat power superior to all
organizations.
It’s their instinct to always attack first because
they believe that they will have the advantage
of winning. However, their fighting is rarely
used in protracted battles or battles against
large numbers of trained troops. Their victory
depends on being the first to spot the enemy
and the first to flee.
Each member was assigned a subordinate unit according to combat, search,
and procurement roles. In addition, combat units receive preferential
treatment compared to non-combat units. Although nominally, the cadres
and units are divided, virtually all decisions are made by Jack Grey.
They mostly live in cars
and motorcycles and
prefer to stay in one
place for a short time.
As a result, the majority
of Jack’N Boyz has
converted camping cars
or buses into temporary
residence facilities.
Their leader, Jack Grey was the state sheriff of Dallas.
He had a happy, harmonious family life after the war. His wife
and kids were more important to him than anything else.
However, the happiness of his life didn’t last long. One day he
tragically lost his family to a violent gang.
Jack gradually transforms into a different person due to his
overwhelming guilt over being unable to protect his family.
Mobility is a priority for Jack’N Boyz. They ride
motorcycles and drive classic Mustang-like
muscle cars. They dress in long, dark coats and
hats, and their small patterns hang from their
hats or coats like pins.
Jack’N Boyz consists of about 100 to
150 people, including multi-ethnic
people, criminals, ex-military, and
mercenaries between the ages of 20
and 35. Their own free culture is
intended to be buried beneath their
weapons and past.
Jack’N Boyz is an organization of outlaws
led by criminal Jack Grey, who escaped
Fidelia’s Prison. Most of the initial
members are from the Fidelian Empire,
and they were sentenced to death under
the substantial laws of the Empire and
escaped with Jack Grey while serving
their sentences.
